The following are the chief towns and their populations in 1880: —Omaha, 30,518;
                    Lincoln (the State capital), 13,083; Nebraska City, 4183; Plattsmouth, 4175;
                    Beatrice, 3386; Grand Island, 3550; and Hastings, 2817. All these towns have
                    greatly increased, and some of them, like Hastings, have doubled their
                    populations since 1880.
